{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01R2mGkJKs2BrfuukKkEQ6B3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have all the data. Let me analyze the key compliance observations before writing the report.\n\nKey findings from inspection:\n- **RBAC drift**: live `spark-pi-role` grants `pods` (create/delete/update/patch/...) but the `last-applied-configuration` annotation only declared services/configmaps/persistentvolumeclaims — an undeclared privilege beyond the intended manifest.\n- **Empty securityContext** on both deployments and the Job (`securityContext: {}`) — no runAsNonRoot, no readOnlyRootFilesystem, no dropped capabilities, no allowPrivilegeEscalation:false.\n- **No NetworkPolicy** in the namespace.\n- Positives: resource requests/limits set, pinned image tag, dedicated (non-default) ServiceAccount, scoped namespaced Role.\n\nLet me write the findings and create the ConfigMap."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8938,"cache_read_input_tokens":25236,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8938},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d6c52768-96b5-407d-aca0-093133e9d1a1","uuid":"50018e47-513a-44f4-9f41-aed863516cb2","request_id":"req_011CcAdABRzZEEQMBE6Y86RE"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01R2mGkJKs2BrfuukKkEQ6B3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01T3GuDUj9L1ytnn4jCabgdx","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /tmp/findings.txt <<'EOF'\nCOMPLIANCE AUDIT — namespace: spark-pi\nAudit date: 2026-06-18 | Mode: READ-ONLY (no changes made to live cluster)\nScope: RBAC, resource limits, image provenance, job/pod security context, network policy.\n\n=====================================================================\nA. CORRECTLY CONFIGURED (PASS)\n=====================================================================\n1. Dedicated ServiceAccount: workloads (spark-master, spark-worker, spark-pi\n   Job) all run under the non-default ServiceAccount \"spark-pi\" rather than\n   the namespace \"default\" SA. Good least-privilege identity separation.\n2. Namespaced RBAC: access is granted via a namespaced Role\n   (\"spark-pi-role\") + RoleBinding (\"spark-pi-role-binding\"), not a\n   ClusterRole. Blast radius is confined to the spark-pi namespace.\n3. RoleBinding subject is correctly scoped to ServiceAccount spark-pi in\n   namespace spark-pi (no wildcard / group-wide grant).\n4. Resource governance: spark-master, spark-worker and the spark-pi Job each\n   declare BOTH requests (cpu 200m / mem 512Mi) and limits (cpu 500m /\n   mem 1Gi). No unbounded containers observed.\n5. Image tag pinning: all containers use an explicit version tag\n   apache/spark:3.5.3 (no \":latest\"); imagePullPolicy IfNotPresent.\n6. Job hardening basics: spark-pi Job sets backoffLimit:0 and\n   restartPolicy:Never (no silent retry loops); it completed successfully.\n\n=====================================================================\nB. GAPS / FINDINGS (REMEDIATION CANDIDATES)\n=====================================================================\n[HIGH] RBAC drift / over-privilege — undeclared \"pods\" grant.\n   The LIVE spark-pi-role rules grant the \"pods\" resource with verbs\n   create,get,list,watch,delete,update,patch. However the role's\n   kubectl.kubernetes.io/last-applied-configuration annotation only declares\n   services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims. => The live Role has been\n   widened beyond its source manifest (configuration drift). A SparkPi\n   workload does not need create/delete/patch on pods; this grant would let a\n   compromised spark-pi SA manipulate arbitrary pods in the namespace.\n   Recommend: remove \"pods\" from the role (or reconcile manifest vs cluster).\n\n[HIGH] Missing pod/container securityContext on all workloads.\n   spark-master Deployment, spark-worker Deployment, and the spark-pi Job all\n   have securityContext: {} (empty) at pod level and NO container-level\n   securityContext. Consequently NONE of the following hardening controls are\n   set: runAsNonRoot, runAsUser/runAsGroup, allowPrivilegeEscalation:false,\n   readOnlyRootFilesystem, capabilities drop ALL, seccompProfile. Containers\n   may run as root (uid 0) with privilege escalation permitted. Does not meet\n   restricted Pod Security Standards.\n\n[MEDIUM] No NetworkPolicy in the namespace.\n   `kubectl get networkpolicy -n spark-pi` returns none. With no default-deny,\n   all pod-to-pod and ingress/egress traffic is permitted. Spark master/worker\n   ports (7077, 8080, 8081) are reachable from any pod in the cluster.\n   Recommend a default-deny + explicit-allow policy set.\n\n[LOW] Image provenance not digest-pinned.\n   Images are tag-pinned (apache/spark:3.5.3) but not pinned by sha256 digest,\n   and there is no admission/signature verification evidence. A mutated tag\n   could be pulled on a future node. Recommend digest pinning + image signing.\n\n[INFO] Note: an unrelated ConfigMap \"rollback-rehearsal\" is present in the\n   namespace; not in audit scope, recorded for awareness.\n\n=====================================================================\nSUMMARY: 6 controls PASS. 4 gaps (2 HIGH, 1 MEDIUM, 1 LOW).\nMost significant: RBAC drift granting undeclared pods access, and the complete\nabsence of securityContext hardening across all Spark workloads.\nRemediation to be planned separately. No live configuration was modified\nduring this audit.\nEOF\nkubectl -n spark-pi create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat /tmp/findings.txt)\"","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8938,"cache_read_input_tokens":25236,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8938},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d6c52768-96b5-407d-aca0-093133e9d1a1","uuid":"a4c76088-be56-40da-bf15-157112c8023f","request_id":"req_011CcAdABRzZEEQMBE6Y86RE"}
